      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i need help writing a rejection email for a candidate. They made it to the final round for a senior dev role here in Austin, so it's a tough one. They were really strong in system design and had great culture fit, but we just went with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud stack. Can you draft something professional and kind so we don't burn a bridge?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can help you draft a rejection email that's both professional and kind. Here's a sample:\n\n\"Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the status of your application for the Senior Developer role at [Company Name]. We were truly impressed with your exceptional system design skills and your enthusiasm for our company culture. Unfortunately, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns more closely with our specific cloud stack requirements at this time.\n\nPlease know that this decision is in no way a reflection on your abilities or potential as a developer. You would be a great fit for many organizations, and we have no doubt that you will land an opportunity that's a perfect match for your skills.\n\nWe appreciate the time and effort you invested in our interview process, and we wish you the best of luck in your job search. If you have any questions or would like to discuss further, please don't hesitate to reach out.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\"\n\nThis email aims to be kind and respectful while still conveying the reasons for the rejection. By acknowledging the candidate's strengths and expressing confidence in their future prospects, you can maintain a positive tone and leave a good impression.",
